Anthony Scotina

Bio

Hello, and thanks for stopping by! I am currently a Principal Biostatistician at Koneksa Health, where I focus on developing analytical methods for longitudinal data from digital health technologies.

Before joining Koneksa, I was an Assistant Professor and Data Science Program Director in the Division of Computer, Data, and Mathematical Sciences at Simmons University.

I received my Ph.D.in Biostatistics from the Brown University School of Public Health in 2018, where I focused on causal inference methodology for observational studies with multiple treatment arms.

My current research interests include:

  • Digital health technologies
  • Longitudinal data
  • Causal inference
  • Statistics education
  • Data visualization

Experience

Koneksa Health

  • Principal Biostatistician | February 2024 - present

  • Senior Statistician | August 2022 - January 2024

Simmons University

  • Assistant Professor of Statistics | July 2018 - August 2022

Education

Brown University | Providence, RI

  • Ph.D.in Biostatistics | September 2014 - May 2018

University of Massachusetts, Amherst | Amherst, MA

  • M.S. in Statistics | September 2012 - May 2014

College of the Holy Cross | Worcester, MA

  • A.B. in Mathematics and Psychology | September 2008 - May 2012
